race.comment: CALIDO MAGIC (9) brings good city and provincial form to this race. Made up a little ground without threatening last start over this distance at Hawkesbury. Placed two from three at this track and looks well in on 55kgs. Hard to beat in a competitive race. CODE IN TIME (1) has led for home but been overhauled comfortably in his last two runs, both over longer trips in Brisbane. Back to this trip for the first time in a while but from a good gate with blinkers back on he is sure to run a cheeky race. SHE'S EXOTIC (6) missed the kick and failed to recover over this trip at Doomben recently. Handy mare who has won four from seven so leave her out at your peril. QUEEN OF A HAND (7) has won three from three this prep. Meets better types today but with just 53kgs after the claim is certainly one to consider. BRING ME KASH (2) has started to find some form and cannot be ruled out with the aid of the inside alley.
